Title: Privilege Escalation: Low Privilege User Can Modify Super Admin-Restricted Client Management Data
Description: A low privilege user can modify sensitive client management data, which should be restricted to Super Admins. This vulnerability allows unauthorized users to change critical information related to client accounts, such as user details, settings, or configurations. The improper enforcement of access control leads to significant risks for data integrity and potential misuse.

Impact:

Unauthorized users can modify sensitive client data, leading to data integrity violations.
Potential for data manipulation, resulting in business disruptions, incorrect records, or malicious changes.
Loss of trust and data accuracy in the client management system.
Recommendation:

Implement strong access control mechanisms to ensure only Super Admins can modify client management data.
Enforce server-side permission checks and role-based access control (RBAC) to prevent unauthorized modifications.
Conduct security audits and access control reviews to ensure that critical functionality is adequately protected.
